Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:05 AM Defendant Joseph E Vazquez Rosa in court.  District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Julian Marrufo.  Defendant requests an extension as he is speaking to an attorney and needs time to retain them.  Defendant requests 30 days and further states he has not been evaluated by the Public Defenders Office but does not believe he would qualify.  The State has no objection.  The Court will allow an adjournment for 30 days for status of counsel. Court tolled time limits for preliminary hearing.
Hearing scheduled for November 3, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing. If DNA sample has not been taken from the defendant, the Court orders sample to be taken;  and it may be expunged under 165.77(4) Wis. Statutes. 
 Defendant is not to have any violent contact with Victim A listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney.  Defendant is not to reside with Victim A and is not to have any physical contact with Victim A unless its through marriage counseling.  Defendant is not to discuss the case with Victim A.

3:22 PM Defendant Joseph E Vazquez Rosa in court, in custody.  Attorney Cassandra A Miller Ms. in court for Joseph E Vazquez Rosa. A ttorney appears as friend of the court.  District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Jack Riederer.  Defendant was not evaluated by the public defender's office, as Attorney Miller was told the defendant was not in custody today.  Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint. Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties. Court advises of right to an attorney. Court tolled time limits for preliminary hearing.
Hearing scheduled for October 6, 2022 at 10:00 am.
